    <paragraphs xml:id="sec-1-2-reading">
      <title>Reading</title>
      <p>
        This section is all about considering the effect of specifying order on the real numbers. Pay attention to how things are defined, because it is a bit unusual: we first define a set of "positive numbers", and then we use those to define what it means to say <m>a \leq b</m>
        <ul>
          <li>Axiom II</li>
          <li>definition of positive and negative numbers</li>
          <li>exercise 1.3.1</li>
          <li>definition 1.3.2</li>
          <li>exercise 1.3.3</li>
